prints.title: Medical Device Prototype Housing

images.alt: Medical Device Prototype Housing - PETG 3D print showing Prototype housing for at-home tonometer project. R...
Medical Device Prototype Housing - PETG 3D print showing Prototype housing for at-home tonometer project. R...
Medical Device Prototype Housing - PETG 3D print showing Prototype housing for at-home tonometer project. R...

prints.notes: Prototype housing for at-home tonometer project. Required biocompatible PETG material and precise tolerances for sensor integration. Multiple iterations to achieve proper fit with electronic components.
prints.learnings: Discovered importance of print orientation for structural integrity in medical applications. Wall thickness critical for durability.
prints.applications: Medical device prototyping, healthcare hardware development

prints.notes: Custom cable routing system for development workstation. Designed with snap-fit connections for easy reconfiguration as setup evolves.
prints.learnings: PLA perfect for desk accessories - strong enough but easy to print. Snap-fit tolerances require precise calibration.
prints.applications: Workspace organization, rapid prototyping of functional designs

prints.notes: Designed for video calls and code review sessions. Multiple angle positions with secure phone grip. Optimized print orientation to minimize supports.
prints.learnings: Importance of considering use case during design phase. Angle calculations matter for actual ergonomic benefit.
